<TEXT>
a nineyearold east german boy 
was killed and several of his six companions injured when they 
tried to flee to west germany through a czechoslovak border post 
the staterun ctk news agency said 
the agency said the incident occurred early tuesday when a 
sovietmade volga sedan tried to ram a barrier at the 
czechoslovakwest german border at strazny about 100 miles 
southwest of prague 
seven east germans four of them children were traveling in the 
car ctk said the unidentified driver tried to smash through the 
border barrier but crashed slicing the roof off the car it added 
a nineyearold boy was killed and an unspecified number of 
other people injured it said adding that all the survivors were 
detained by czechoslovak border guards 
the east germans were not identified and ctk did not report 
their hometown or any other details abot their background saying 
only that the case was under investigation 
