<TEXT>
there was weeping on family ties as the 
series closed out a sevenyear run on nbc sunday but the network 
wasnt crying this week when it broke cbs quartercenturyold 
record winning ratings streak 
cbs won 46 weeks in a row in the 196263 season as of sunday 
nbc had been in first place for 47 straight weeks in the ac 
nielsen co ratings and added to the honor by taking the top 11 
spots in the rankings the first time a network has done that in 10 
years 
nbc prepared a list of nostalgic trivia to illustrate how long a 
26yearold record is in 196263 the tonight show starring 
johnny carson premiered the new york mets lost 120 games in 
their first season marilyn monroe died and there was no such 
thing as vcrs personal computers the super bowl remote control 
tylenol or people magazine 
this recordbreaking performance assuming nobody has made 
another clerical mistake really belongs to the talented writers 
producers directors and actors whose consistently fine work has 
won the hearts and viewing habits of the american public said 
nbc entertainment president brandon tartikoff 
his statement referred to nbcs premature declaration a few 
weeks ago that it had set a record until cbs pointed out that the 
record actually ran to 46 weeks 
the special onehour finale of family ties was last weeks 
no 1 show with a 208 rating and 35 share it was broadcast 
opposite the final episode of abcs moonlighting which had 
lost viewers so dramatically it had dwindled to third from the 
bottom in the rankings 
nbc which has won four seasons in a row won last week with an 
average primetime rating of 157 abc whose massive miniseries 
war and remembrance took up much of the week with mediocre 
ratings had an 118 cbs had an 113 
each rating point equals 904000 households with television the 
share is a percentage of sets in use 
the rest of the top 10 were all nbcs golden girls the 
cosby show top gun jackee special cheers in the 
heat of the night unsolved mysteries la law and 
hunter nbcs sunday movie ferris buellers day off 
ranked 11th nbc said the last time a network had the top 11 shows 
was 1979 when abc had the miniseries roots ii 
the fivepart conclusion of abcs war and remembrance built 
audience each night but after sunday nights conclusion which 
ranked 18th it wound up with an average rating of 148 and a 23 
the first 17 hours of the winds of war sequel ran in 
november and had an average rating of 186 and a 29 share 
the 10 lowestrated shows last week were jesse hawkes 
murder by moonlight west 57th hard time on planet 
earth north and south book two part one kareem 
abduljabbar incredible sunday moonlighting a man 
called hawk and the jim henson hour 
in the news ratings abc world news tonight won the week 
with an average rating of 102 and a 21 share the cbs evening 
news had a 94 and 19 nbc nightly news had a 90 and 19 
share 
