upon the end abolition of apartheid we must now reach agreement 
on the means 
the reagan administration fought and lost a bitter battle with 
congress in 1986 over sanctions on south africa 
kennedy said that instead of rushing to refight old battles 
we intend to seek new possibilities for cooperating with the 
administration in us policy toward south africa 
national party leader fw de klerk who is expected to become 
south africas next leader once president pw botha retires in 
