republicans are planning to challenge house 
action on a savings and loan bailout bill approved by its banking 
committee after democrats changed the wording in a controversial 
provision requiring sampls to subsidize lowincome housing 
committee chairman henry b gonzalez dtexas said the 
alteration in the 600page bill reported to the full house on 
tuesday two weeks after it was approved by the panel was only a 
technical change to define the clear intent of the committee 
republicans however called it a power grab that was done 
without a vote and promised to fight it when the legislation is 
referred to the house rules committee and on the house floor 
the language in the report differs markedly from the language 
as reported from the committee said assistant house gop whip 
robert walker of pennsylvania substantive sections of the bill 
have been unilaterally changed by the chairman 
the uproar is over a provision authored by gonzalez that the 
banking committees 20 republicans unanimously opposed two weeks 
ago basically it would require sampls to subsidize belowmarket 
mortgage rates for lowincome home buyers by 75 million a year 
from 1990 to 1994 and by 150 million a year in 1995 and thereafter 
according to consumer groups the measure could provide 100000 
lowincome home buyers with mortgages that are 2 percentage points 
below market rates 
if were going to save a savings and loan system that has any 
recognizable right to that name then you have to do something 
about making housing affordable said gonzalez 
republicans had opposed the measure as social engineering 
and said it did not belong in a bill in which taxpayers are being 
asked to pay more than 200 billion over the next 30 years to cover 
bad loans made by sampls in the 1980s 
the dispute was reignited last week when congressional tax 
experts told the taxwriting house ways and means committee that 
the lowincome housing provision looks like a tax setting off 
claims that the banking committee had exceeded its authority 
its a usurpation of this committees jurisdiction by another 
committee charged rep bill archer of texas the ranking 
republican on ways and means 
ways and means chairman dan rostenkowski dill persuaded his 
committee to defer striking the provision which has widescale 
support among democrats while he and gonzalez attempted to work 
out a compromise the ways and means committee is scheduled to 
formally adopt the change on thursday 
rep barney frank dmass said an accord retaining the 
provision but changing its language in a small way was reached 
through mediation by house speaker jim wrights office and rep 
charles rangel dny chairman of the ways and means subcommittee 
on select revenue measures 
as gonzalez measure was approved by the committee the 12 
district federal home loan banks that borrow funds for and are 
owned by the industry would have to devote 5 percent of their net 
earnings or profits or a minimum of 75 million a year until 
1994 for the new lowincome mortgages 
for 1994 the contribution was 6 percent of net earnings or a 
minimum 90 million and from 1995 on it was 10 percent of net 
earnings or a minimum 150 million a year 
