the stark a 3600ton missile frigate was nearly sunk on may 
17 1987 by two frenchmade exocet missiles fired by an iraqi 
warplane while the ship was conducting what us officials called 
routine duty in the central gulf 
the attack killed 37 of its crew of 220 and injured 21 iraq 
later apologized saying the pilot of the f1 mirage had mistaken 
the us frigate for an iranian ship 
the incident spurred the united states to expand its forces in 
the gulf to protect usflagged shipping from the tanker war 
