the revolutionary leader robespierres own draft of 
frances first constitution goes on the auction block next month 
along with other documents from the bloody events of 200 years ago 
the 57page manuscript to be sold june 12 by paris auctioneer 
jacques tajan contains countless annotations in maximilien 
robespierres own hand on various aspects of the first constitution 
prepared in 1791 by the national assembly 
