may 30 before a federal judge in indianapolis 
the mosaics come from the panayia kanakaria byzantine church in 
the village of lythrangomi in turkishoccupied northern cyprus 
cypriot officials say the mosaics were probably removed in 1979 
five years after the turks invaded cyprus 
the dealer peg l goldberg bought the mosaics in switzerland 
for 12 million and is trying to sell them to the j paul getty 
museum in malibu calif for 20 million 
this is going to be interesting case said constance 
lowenthal executive director of the international foundation for 
art research a new yorkbased group dedicated to combating forgery 
and theft of artworks 
the dispute already known to the art world has reached the 
upper levels of the administration william von raab the head of 
the customs service was briefed on the case as were officials 
from the state department 
both the government of cyprus and golberg have hired highpriced 
attorneys and lobbyists to defend them goldberg has enlisted help 
from two former aides to sen richard lugar rind 
goldberg 50 a hamilton county ind commissioner and a 
private art dealer followed all the proper procedures when she 
bought the mosaics indirectly through a turkish art dealer 
according to louis gerig her public relations consultant in 
indianapolis 
i feel confident she has done all the right things said 
gerig a former aide to lugar and assistant press secretary to 
former president reagan gerig was also a special assistant to the 
commissioner of the customs service 
after goldberg bought the mosaics and brought them to the united 
states in july gerig and jeffrey bergner another exlugar aide 
checked with state department officials to ensure there were no 
problems associated with the treasures gerig said 
gerig said he was assured there were none goldberg however 
never checked with the cyprus embassy to find out the status of the 
mosaics embassy officials said 
then goldberg through her agent offered the mosaics to the 
getty museum after that marion true the museums curator of 
antiquities contacted authorities in cyprus who said the 
antiquities had been stolen according to a deposition in the case 
although customs agents had allowed the mosaics to come into the 
country the service opened an investigation into the case early 
this year said gerig who said he went to see von raab about the 
issue 
last february von raab signed a letter saying it appeared the 
antiquities were brought into the united states properly 
the chief counsel here could not find criminal intent she 
in good faith declared the items said dennis schimkoski von 
raabs spokesman 
in march attorneys for cyprus sought a restraining order to 
prevent goldberg from selling the mosaics 
with the trial slated for later this month a delegation from 
cyprus arrived here to consult with attorneys seeking to prove in 
court the antiquities were stolen from the island said marios 
evriviades a spokesman for the embassy 
although the united states and cyprus have a treaty covering 
stolen artworks the pact was not ratified until 1983 it does not 
apply to items removed before that time said ann guthriehingston 
director of the cultural properties advisory board of the us 
information agency 
</TEXT>
