among the problems frequently cited as examples were the 
inadequacy of the road system except in koror and the limitations 
of the hospital system 
in view of the considerable sums of money spent by the 
administering authority in the past in the field of economic and 
social development and of additional commitments under the 
proposed new status arrangements the mission considers that this 
attitude largely reflects tactical considerations 
the complaints were aimed at obtaining additional concessions 
from the us executive and legislative branches at a time when 
delicate negotiations have just begun between the united states 
authorities and palauan officials the mission declared 
in 1988the 15000 people of palau received about 33 million in 
us aid jeanmichel gaussot of france and j stephen smith of 
britain led the mission for the trusteeship council which is 
evaluating palaus progress toward adopting the proposed compact of 
free association with the united states 
that agreement would make the islands selfgoverning but leave 
the united states in charge of defense with the right to use land 
for any purpose it deemed necessary in exchange for 1 billion in 
aid over 75 years about 460 million of the us aid would be paid 
in the first 15 years 
us officials deny planning to establish military bases last 
year however adm william crowe chairman of the joint chiefs 
told a congressional committee palau would be one of the first or 
priority areas we would have to look at if the united states lost 
its bases in the philippines 
palaus constitution bars nuclear weapons and nuclear power from 
its territory a majority of palauans have favored the compact in 
several referendums but it has not won the 75 percent needed to 
overrule the constitutional ban 
the united states captured the archipelago and other pacific 
islands from japan in world war ii it consists of 200 islands 
totaling 192 square miles about 500 miles east of the philippine 
island of mindanao 
