<TEXT>
a factfinders report wednesday urged 
striking teachers to end the 3dayold walkout that has crippled 
education for more than a halfmillion students in the nations 
secondlargest school district 
the report concluded the los angeles unified school districts 
offer will provide a teacher compensation package which is among 
the best in los angeles county the state of california and in the 
entire united states 
the teachers had contended the district was topheavy with 
administrators and concealing it financial reserves but the report 
concluded that the district spends less on administrators and 
wasnt hiding surplus funds 
the report said the district spends only 495 percent of its 
total expense on salaries for administrators the average in the 20 
largest unified school districts in california is 63 percent 
the report was prepared by lawyer geraldine randall who began 
investigating the dispute last march when the 16month contract 
negotiation reached an impasse 
she was selected jointly by the los angeles unified school 
district and the teachers union but wayne johnson president of 
united teacherlos angeles dismissed the conclusions saying the 
