short said jackie rogers jr a character he developed on 
sctv as one of the gushing guests on the sammy maudlin 
show is a grotesque character who symbolizes everything thats 
bad about show business when he tries to be deep hes merely 
pompous you want somebody to punch him in the head or throw a pie 
in his face 
ed grimley was originated onstage at second city hes a 
conglomeration of people ive known short said ed maintains 
himself with a spirit of enthusiasm he runs a gamut of emotions in 
five minutes hes like a guy smelling the roses after a heart 
attack except he hasnt had a heart attack 
short whose latest movie is three fugitives has a film 
development deal with disney studios 
its hard to find something thats good and something that you 
havent done he said im also looking at a broadway musical 
the ideal career for me would be able to do a tv special a movie 
and a play every year when i was an actor in canada you didnt do 
just one medium you did everything and it broadened you 
short moved his home from toronto to los angeles last year i 
always had a home here and a home in toronto he said weve 
got two children and two years ago we were flying back for 
christmas and the kids were screaming i thought why are we doing 
this for our value system if youre not from la it can be very 
healthy to live elsewhere this is the war zone and you go home to 
rest but the reality is i no longer felt it was necessary to go 
home 
hes married to nancy dolman who was gilda radners understudy 
when short and radner were doing godspell 
short was born in hamilton ontario where he said he grew up 
watching lucille ball dick van dyke and jackie gleason 
those were the three big influences when i was young he 
said i was fascinated by the way gleason could play ralph 
kramden and be so real it always amazed me how far you could 
go within the reality a character without any reality is pretty 
dull 
