<TEXT>
the temptation to share inside information about a 
corporate takeover apparently proved too much for a 24yearold 
paralegal at a prestigious law firm the securities and exchange 
commission says 
in a civil complaint filed tuesday in us district court in 
boston the sec charged that kerry a hurton handled confidential 
papers about plans for a 230 million buyout of a southern 
department store chain while she was working in the boston office 
of skadden arps slate meagher amp flom in 1987 
by passing information about the takeover to friends and 
acquaintances the sec said ms hurton prompted at least five 
people to buy a total of 65020 shares of stock in the birmingham 
ala chain of parisian inc at an average price of 18 a share in 
june and july 1987 
when a buyout by hooker corp was announced later that summer 
parisians stock shot up to more than 30 a share the sec said 
the complaint seeks to force the defendants to return alleged 
profits of 823825 and pay up to three times that amount in 
penalties lawyers for the defendants said they maintain they did 
nothing wrong 
attorney john wall who represents ms hurton said she has 
agreed to sign a consent decree in which she does not acknowledge 
any past wrongdoing but agrees to refrain from passing inside 
information in the future 
i had asked the sec to file the consent decree simultaneously 
with the complaint wall said but apparently they want the 
publicity to be onesided 
the sec said ms hurton worked for skadden arps a leading new 
york law firm from october 1986 to july 1988 during that time 
the firm represented hooker an australian retailing and real 
estate company 
peter p mullen an executive partner in the 970lawyer firm 
said skadden arps cooperated with the sec probe and suspended ms 
hurton in may 1988 as soon as we learned she was under serious 
suspicion he added that she was fired a few weeks later when 
she refused to cooperate with the sec investigation 
from our point of view we feel aggrieved because in effect 
she appropriated information she shouldnt have and flagrantly 
violated our policies if in fact the charges are correct he 
said 
hooker completed the acquisition of parisian for 3065 a share 
or a total of about 230 million in april 1988 mullen said he did 
not believe the insider trading had any effect on the deal 
parisian has 16 stores in alabama texas georgia and florida 
the secs yearlong investigation was sparked by a tip from a 
private individual said john sturc the agencys associate 
director for enforcement in washington 
in its complaint the sec said ms hurton passed the information 
to a close personal friend eric laboz of new york city and 
his former roommate at boston university jonathan r beck of north 
hills ny 
