britains civil aviation authority said wednesday 
there is nothing basically wrong with boeings new 747400 
series jets but that the american company has not met modern 
european standards 
there is nothing basically wrong with the aircraft said a 
caa spokesman speaking anonymously in keeping with british custom 
but you can liken the situation to that of a motorist who 
some years ago would not have needed rear seat belts but who now 
does 
the us regulatory body the federal aviation administration 
has approved the new aircraft but european aviation authorities 
are threatening to withhold airworthiness certificates for the 
planes unless boeing agrees to a number of design changes 
without the certificates the planes cannot be used for scheduled 
commercial flights 
british airways which has ordered 19 of the new planes said 
wednesday it remains confident it will soon be operating them 
