percent of the revenues from the groups first two releases after 
omni has recouped the advance it paid the artists but atms first 
release didnt sell enough copies to bring any money back to the 
college he said 
since the only area of recordcompany management not covered is 
studio recording the class begins its star search with a call for 
productionquality tapes 
after the students select an act aemmp contracts with a record 
maker to press the vinyl copies a tape duplicator to make the 
cassettes and an albumjacket company to package the product 
with only a 1500 budget the students often rely on the good 
will of manufacturers like agi inc a suburban chicago albumcover 
manufacturer that has donated services to aemmp since the class was 
created 
