<TEXT>
the us dollar rose sharply in europe on 
wednesday benefiting from a smallerthanexpected us trade 
deficit in march 
gold prices in europe dropped to a 33month low while silver 
was trading at a 26month low 
in late european trading the dollar had moved to a 34month 
high against the swiss franc a 32month high against the italian 
lira a 30month high against the french franc and a 28month high 
against the dutch guilder 
in london the british pound slumped to a 20month low dropping 
to 16140 from 16398 late tuesday 
the dollar also rose in tokyo to a 18month high against the 
japanese yen closing up 070 yen at 13770 yen later in london 
it pushed up further to 13895 yen 
after fluctuating in a narrow range early wednesday the dollar 
surged when the us government reported an unexpectedly narrow 
trade deficit of 89 billion in march and revised the february 
deficit to 98 billion down from 109 billion 
economists had anticipated a 10 billion deficit for the most 
recent month 
since there was no sign of central bank interventions 
everybody was buying said a trader in frankfurt west germany 
selected late dollar rates in europe compared with late tuesday 
19675 west german marks up from 19426 17580 swiss francs up 
