<TEXT>
minorco sa the south africacontrolled mining 
concern said wednesday it will continue pursuing natural resources 
companies despite its failed 59 billion bid for consolidated gold 
fields plc 
luxembourgbased minorco on tuesday conceded defeat in its 
eightmonth takeover attempt for gold fields in a deal that would 
have created the worlds largest gold company 
the concession came after a federal judge in new york refused to 
lift an order blocking minorco from acquiring more than 30 percent 
of gold fields before the bid was to expire under british takeover 
regulations 
minorco which is 60 percent owned by the oppenheimer familys 
anglo american corp and de beers consolidated mines ltd gold and 
diamond mining interests said its board would meet next month to 
decide the companys next move 
minorco remains the largest single shareholder in the british 
mining giant with a 299 percent stake and deciding whether to 
hold on to or sell it likely will be on the boards agenda 
we will now energetically implement our strategy of 
transforming minorco into an operating company minorco chief 
executive sir michael edwardes said 
minorco had pursued gold fields to fulfill that goal 
minorco is now a familiar name in the market both in the uk 
and overseas and has a very positive future edwardes said 
keith irons a minorco vice president said he expects the 
company to progress toward its strategic goal of being a global 
business operating in natural resources mainly through 100 percent 
owned subsidiaries 
that means minorco might increase or sell one or more of its 
existing partial stakes 
besides the gold fields stake which represents about onethird 
of minorcos 4 billion in assets the company also owns 30 percent 
of engelhard corp and 48 percent of adobe resources corp both of 
the united states 
minorco also holds 56 percent of inspiration resources corp of 
the united states but controls just 42 percent of the votes 
in britain the company has a 36 percent stake in charter 
consolidated plc the company has 1 billion in cash and borrowing 
facilities of 23 billion good until september 1991 irons said 
adding that minorco would continue to focus on north america and 
europe 
