the stock market staged a moderate advance today 
in response to a betterthanexpected report on international trade 
the dow jones average of 30 industrials rose 1429 to 246774 
by 2 pm on wall street 
gainers outnumbered losers by more than 3 to 2 in nationwide 
trading of new york stock exchangelisted issues with 853 up 549 
down and 510 unchanged 
the commerce department reported this morning that the nations 
trade deficit narrowed to 886 billion in march from a 
downwardrevised 982 billion the month before 
advance estimates on wall street had called for a march deficit 
of 10 billion or more 
the news sent the dollar higher in foreign exchange but 
analysts said it got a less exuberant response in the bond and 
stock markets in part because it suggested that the pace of the 
domestic economy might not be slowing as much as had been hoped 
in addition brokers said traders were staying cautious ahead of 
the scheduled report from the government thursday on the consumer 
price index for april 
there is some concern on wall street that the figures will cast 
doubts on the belief that the federal reserve is beginning to 
succeed in its effort to restrain inflation 
gainers among the blue chips included general electric up 1 at 
53 philip morris up 2 at 134 american telephone amp telegraph 
up at 34 and eastman kodak up at 43 
